
Ranger Help for: track
======================

SYNTAX:      track <opponent>
USAGE:       forest,plains,swamp,desert,jungle,hills,road,beach,
             mountain,arctic,barren,outside,underground
SLOT COST:   13
BASE SP:     50 sp
SKILL TYPE:  tracking

SUMMARY:
This skill allows a Ranger to track down opponents like dogs. A Ranger
can set out to track an opponent in any terrain, but once the Ranger
finds the tracks, they may only be intermitent..IE: tracks won't be left
in water terrains. And just remember, because you find a set of
tracks, it doesn't mean its your query. You must look over the tracks
and determine if its your foe from what you know of him or her. Also,
when following a set of tracks, depending how good you are and how clever
your query is, the information you get from tracks might change from
set to set. Don't mess around when tracking an opponent because the
environments in the Domains of Darkwind are ever changing, so tracks
only last for so long and the trail won't go on forever, so you must
be quick on your feet in order to catch a query.

